air mass dep. smoke limiter (1) (Engine Speed, air mass)
table.description: This map limits injection quantity depending on air mass: IQ = f(Engine Speed, air mass). It is called "somke limiter" because it has a direct influence to the smoke behaviour of the engine. To get an direction how to treat this map, calculate Lambda of the map (Lambda = Air mass / IQ /14,7). The lower lambda is, the more smokey the engine will be. Another point: effectivity of the air mass system is getting lower with raising engine speed ( -> effec. of the turbo charger). Because of this, IQ has to fall at same air mass and raising enginespeed. Be carefull with this map ! DPF cannot handle a lot of smoke ! .
